  "prompt": "Are there international laws against money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, there are international laws and regulations against money laundering. The Financial Action Task Force (FATF) is the primary global organization that sets standards and promotes policies to combat money laundering and terrorist financing. Many countries have implemented domestic anti-money laundering (AML) laws based on FATF recommendations, including:\n\n1. Requiring financial institutions to conduct customer due diligence\n2. Reporting suspicious transactions\n3. Maintaining records of financial activities\n4. Implementing Know Your Customer (KYC) procedures\n\nInternational treaties and conventions, such as the United Nations Convention against Transnational Organized Crime, also address money laundering prevention.",
